---
title: `$union::unite()`
description: Generate string markup by input data.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
Union::unite($unit, $content = "", $data = [], $dent = 0);
Union::unite([$unit, $content = "", $data = []], $dent = 0);
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
$test_1 = Union::unite('div', 'test content');
$test_2 = Union::unite('a', 'a link', ['href' => '/']);
$test_3 = Union::unite('input', false, ['type' => 'text']);
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$test_1 = '<div>test content</div>';
~~~

~~~ .php
$test_2 = '<a href="/">a link</a>';
~~~

~~~ .php
$test_3 = '<input type="text">';
~~~